Make the external monitor stay on when the laptop lid is closed:
sudo sed -i '/IgnoreLid=/{s/false/true/}' /etc/UPower/UPower.conf
sudo sed -i '/HandleLidSwitch/{s/#//;s/suspend/ignore/}' /etc/systemd/logind.conf
sudo systemctl restart systemd-logind

Turn on touchpad:
// List all input devices
xinput --list
// Find the touchpad id. In this example, it's 14. List the properties
xinput --list-props 14
// Find the property "tap to click", it will have a number in parentheses. Here it's 366
xinput set-prop 14 366 1

Copy scratchpad script from .local/scripts
